claim.claim-text:
1. A method of preparing a soluble dietary fiber comprising the steps of: 
(i) removing starch and protein from corn hulls; 
(ii) extracting the starch- and protein-removed corn hulls with an alkaline solution, and filtering the alkaline extract through filter cloth; 
(iii) treating the filtrate of step (ii) with cellulase and cellobiase; 
(iv) treating the solution of step (iii) with adsorbent, and filtering it through a membrane filter; and 
(v) purifying the filtrate.
